[?2004huser@2a422e2e1198:~/scheduler$ cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'
[?2004l[?2004h> # DST Bug Fix Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> The scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times (off by 1 hour) for meetings between 2am-3am local time in Europe/Berlin timezone. This occurred specifically during DST (Daylight Saving Time) transitions.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> In `/home/user/scheduler/app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # BUGGY CODE (line 30):
[?2004l[?2004h> berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This incorrectly treated the UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin time, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin time.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## The Fix
[?2004l[?2004h> Changed the conversion to properly handle timezone conversion:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # FIXED CODE (lines 29-32):
